**Overall Meaning:**

"May my mind be filled with auspicious thoughts, those mind, heart, and gods, those divine waters, those sun rays, they moving in the ear and eye."

**Explanation:**

This verse emphasizes the interconnectedness of all things and the divine presence within all aspects of our being. It mentions the mind, heart, gods, water, and sunlight as examples of this divine presence. The verse also suggests that these divine elements are constantly moving and interacting within us, through our senses, thoughts, and emotions. The verse expresses a desire for the mind to be aligned with this divine flow, recognizing and appreciating the presence of the divine in every aspect of our existence. 
